responded: The root cause of the null dereference is that `stdscr` may be NULL when `curses_initscr_called` is true, but the code unconditionally calls `wrefresh(stdscr)` and passes `stdscr` to `PyCursesWindow_New`. If `stdscr` is NULL, this will cause a null pointer dereference.

To fix this, we need to check if `stdscr` is NULL before using it in the block:
```c
if (curses_initscr_called) {
    wrefresh(stdscr);
    return (PyObject *)PyCursesWindow_New(stdscr, NULL);
}
```
If `stdscr` is NULL, we should raise an error and return NULL, similar to how the code handles `win == NULL` after `initscr()`.

Here is the patch:

args.patch:
diff --git a/Modules/_cursesmodule.c b/Modules/_cursesmodule.c
index ece6b13c788..c3ad1a693b7 100644
--- a/Modules/_cursesmodule.c
+++ b/Modules/_cursesmodule.c
@@ -3366,6 +3366,11 @@ _curses_initscr_impl(PyObject *module)
     WINDOW *win;

     if (curses_initscr_called) {
+        if (stdscr == NULL) {
+            _cursesmodule_state *state = get_cursesmodule_state(module);
+            PyErr_SetString(state->error, catchall_NULL);
+            return NULL;
+        }
         wrefresh(stdscr);
         return (PyObject *)PyCursesWindow_New(stdscr, NULL);
     }

